      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LA SMOOCH (1) resumes from a spell of ten weeks after closing off last campaign in good form, the last run being a solid third over 2180m at Kilmore. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw and should be right there at the finish. TRYX VIXEN (7) finished second at Charlton two starts back then did a good job again at her latest appearance over 1690m at Kilmore, beaten 4 metres into third after being close to the pace throughout. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but her recent efforts are good enough to put her right in the finish. I AM MOLLY (6) is a three-year-old filly from the C M Mcswain yard on debut. Placed in a recent trial. Will be right there at the business end. LOOK AT HER (3) disappointed last time when sixth over 1690m at Kilmore. Can do a lot better so worth considering for the multiples.",
